################################################################################
# Woodruff & van Dijk Framework: Prenatal Medication/Substance Exposure Coding
# (ABCD Developmental History Questionnaire – Parent / DHX)
#
# Purpose
# -------
# This script constructs gestational exposure indicators for multiple psychotropic
# medication classes and key prenatal substance exposures using ABCD DHX data.
# Outputs from this script are designed to feed directly into the Woodruff & van Dijk
# causal inference framework (ATT propensity score weighting + weighted outcome models).
#
# We use TWO informants to capture exposure more completely:
#   (1) Rx free-text medication labels (ph_p_dhx__rx__label_00Xa / 00Xb items)
#   (2) Direct DHX substance items (alc/mj/nic/coc/opi/caff stems + quantity fields)
#
# Exposure Timing Definitions
# --------------------------
# DHX timing is operationalized using the questionnaire stem suffix:
#   - "_a" = before knowledge of pregnancy  ("before")
#   - "_b" = after knowledge of pregnancy   ("after")
#   - "any" = before OR after (or pregnancy-wide item for caffeine)
#
# Primary Outputs (high level)
# ----------------------------
# After running this script, MED_DHQ_Data_xlsx contains:
#
#  A) Class-level medication exposure flags derived from Rx free-text
#     - Prenatal anytime exposures: prenatal_<class>_exposure
#     - Timing-specific exposures:  <class>_before, <class>_after
#     - Timing pattern flags:       <class>_before_only, <class>_after_only,
#                                   <class>_before_and_after
#     Classes include:
#       * Antidepressants (overall)
#       * SSRIs
#       * SNRIs
#       * Other antidepressants (non-SSRI, non-SNRI)
#       * Anticonvulsants / mood stabilizers
#       * Stimulants
#       * Sleep aids / sedative-hypnotics
#       * Anxiolytics
#       * Antipsychotics
#       * Opioids
#
#  B) Class-level “which drugs were detected” text summaries (Rx free-text)
#     - <class>_*_drug variables store matched generic/brand terms as a
#       semicolon-delimited string (e.g., "sertraline; zoloft")
#
#  C) Direct prenatal substance exposure flags from DHX structured items
#     - alc_before/after/any
#     - mj_before/after/any
#     - nic_before/after/any
#     - coc_before/after/any
#     - opi_hm_before/after/any (heroin/morphine direct item)
#     - caff_any (pregnancy-wide only; no before/after stems in DHX)
#
#  D) Opioid harmonization across informants
#     - Opioid class flags (opioid_before/after and prenatal_opioid_exposure) are
#       updated to incorporate the direct heroin/morphine DHX item, preventing
#       under-ascertainment when opioids were not typed into Rx free-text.
#
#  E) Drug-specific binary indicators (Rx free-text)
#     - For each medication in drug_patterns, create:
#         <drug>_before, <drug>_after, <drug>_any
#       to support more granular sensitivity analyses (e.g., sertraline-only).
#
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Required Input Data
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The script assumes a data.frame named MED_DHQ_Data_xlsx exists in memory and
# includes at minimum the following variables:
#
# Identifiers / Metadata
#   - participant_id              (unique participant identifier)
#   - session_id                  (visit identifier; baseline often "ses-00A")
#
# Rx Free-text Medication Labels (DHX)
#   Before pregnancy knowledge ("a" stems):
#     - ph_p_dhx__rx__label_001a
#     - ph_p_dhx__rx__label_002a
#     - ph_p_dhx__rx__label_003a
#     - ph_p_dhx__rx__label_004a
#   After pregnancy knowledge ("b" stems):
#     - ph_p_dhx__rx__label_001b
#     - ph_p_dhx__rx__label_002b
#     - ph_p_dhx__rx__label_003b
#     - ph_p_dhx__rx__label_004b
#
# Direct Substance Items (DHX structured fields)
#   Alcohol:
#     - ph_p_dhx__alc_001a, ph_p_dhx__alc_001b
#     - ph_p_dhx__alc_001a__01/__02/__03, ph_p_dhx__alc_001b__01/__02/__03
#   Marijuana:
#     - ph_p_dhx__mj_001a,  ph_p_dhx__mj_001b
#     - ph_p_dhx__mj_001a__01, ph_p_dhx__mj_001b__01
#   Nicotine/tobacco:
#     - ph_p_dhx__nic_001a, ph_p_dhx__nic_001b
#     - ph_p_dhx__nic_001a__01, ph_p_dhx__nic_001b__01
#   Cocaine/crack:
#     - ph_p_dhx__coc_001a, ph_p_dhx__coc_001b
#     - ph_p_dhx__coc_001a__01, ph_p_dhx__coc_001b__01
#   Heroin/morphine (direct opioid informant):
#     - ph_p_dhx__opi_001a, ph_p_dhx__opi_001b
#     - ph_p_dhx__opi_001a__01, ph_p_dhx__opi_001b__01
#   Caffeine (pregnancy-wide item only):
#     - ph_p_dhx__caff_001
#     - ph_p_dhx__caff_001__01/__02/__03
#
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Key Implementation Notes
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# * Medication class exposures are derived by searching Rx free-text label fields
#   for predefined generic/brand term dictionaries using case-insensitive matching.
# * Timing-specific “before/after” exposure flags are computed separately from the
#   corresponding "_a" and "_b" Rx label columns.
# * Binary exposure flags are coded as 0/1 integers; missing is recoded to 0 after
#   detection to avoid NA propagation in downstream models.
# * Direct substance exposures use both the Yes/No stem and quantity fields; any
#   positive indication is treated as exposed.
# * Opioid class exposure is harmonized by merging Rx free-text detection with the
#   direct heroin/morphine DHX item.
#
# Collaborator Access
# -------------------
# Collaborators should email james.woodruff@nyspi.columbia.edu for the data file
# or for guidance on harmonizing DHX fields across ABCD releases.
################################################################################

